<type>(<scope>): <JIRA> <short summary>
  │       │       │       │
  │       │       │       └─⫸ Summary in present tense. Not capitalized. No period at the end.
  │       │       │
  │       │       └─⫸ Jira Issue Id: eg. AIP-212
  │       │
  │       └─⫸ Commit Scope: API|Kafka|Database|global (optional)
  │                          Scope can be anything based on the type of change. If it impacts multiple areas, then it can be global.
  │
  └─⫸ Commit Type: fix|hotfix|refactor|revert|docs|patch|feat|feature|minor|breaking|perf|major

Note: There MUST be a space after the first colon.

Semantic Version:
* breaking|perf|major: non-backwards compatible change (will bump first digit of version number)
* feat|feature|minor: backwards compatible change (will bump middle digit of version number)
* fix|hotfix|refactor|revert|docs|patch: backwards compatible bug fix (will bump last digit of version number)
